HEADWORD: Hidalgo
<hw>Hi*dal"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., contr. fr.
<ets>hijo de algo</ets>, <it>i. e.</it>, son of something;
<ets>hijo</ets> son (fr. LL. <ets>filius</ets>) + <ets>algo</ets>
something, fr. L. <ets>aliquod</ets>. Cf. <er>Fidalgo</er>.]</ety>
<def>A title, denoting a Spanish nobleman of the lower class.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

